The data exchange between an application and the data container for reader configuration parameters in the reader class is realized with overloaded methods which passes a string from the package de.feig.ReaderConfig representing the name of the configuration parameter. All names of reader configuration parameters of all OBIDÂ® readers are unified and divided in hierarchical order in groups and subgroups separated by a dot.

For more general information, please refer to the system manual of the Reader.
